[2] Brazil (Sao Paulo)
Date: Tue 19 Jan 2010
Source: O Globo [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://oglobo.globo.com/cidades/sp/mat/2010/01/20/epidemia-de-dengue-registrada-em-tres-cidades-do-interior-de-sao-paulo-915656842.asp>


Three cities in the interior of Sao Paulo [state] suffer from a
dengue epidemic: Aracatuba, Sao Jose do Rio Preto, and Ribeirao
Preto. in Aracatuba, there have been 335 confirmed [dengue] cases in
January [2010]. Aracatuba has already lived through several dengue
epidemics. The last was in 2007, when more than 1000 cases were
registered. The situation is worrying; action must be take quickly
because everyone is taking [ill], there are dengue cases in
practically every house.

In Sao Jose do Rio Preto, there are now 452 dengue cases this year
[2010]. "We are hiring trucks, we will hire qualified workers, and I
believe that within a week or 2 we will have 600 or 700 people
working in the fight against dengue in the city," said secretary of
health of Sao Jose do Rio Preto, Jose Victor Maniglia.

In Ribeirao Preto, the [number of] confirmed cases of the disease
reached 137. There are another 481 suspected dengue cases.

The state Secretary of Health of Sao Paulo does not yet have the
number of cases of dengue in the state this year. [2010] According to
the Epidemiological Surveillance Center, in 2009, 8148 people in the
state had the disease.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed-port@promedmail.org>

[In an update published on 22 Jan 2010 in Ribeirao Preto Online (in
Portuguese,
<http://www.ribeiraopretoonline.com.br/saude/dengue-atinge-174-pessoas-em-ribeirao-preto/33727>)
the state Secretariat of Health indicated that the epidemiological
situation for dengue has increased daily and in the municipality
there are now 174 confirmed dengue cases and 557 suspected cases
awaiting laboratory results. Inspectors were denied access to about
28 percent of the houses to be visited and the city government may
seek court action to obtain access to these localities.

