[4] Brazil (Goias)
Date: Tue 19 Jan 2010
Source: G1 [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://g1.globo.com/Noticias/Brasil/0,,MUL1453430-5598,00-POSTOS+DE+SAUDE+DE+GOIAS+DEVEM+RECEBER+TENDAS+PARA+PACIENTES+COM+DENGUE.html>


Goias is among the 5 cities on alert against dengue and the situation
is worrying. The number of cases of the disease is increasing greatly
since the end of last year [2009]. According to the Ministry of
Health, the other states confronting difficulties in combating dengue
are Rondonia, Mato Grosso, Mato Grosso do Sul, and Acre.

In the last 6 weeks of 2009, the dengue cases reported in Goias
increased 350 percent. Just in the 1st 15 days of January [2010],
there were around 1300 cases, an increase of almost 200 percent in
relation to the same period last year [2009]. In the Goiania city and
municipality the increase was 1200 percent.

The city has health posts that are improvising wards to attend to so
many people. Conditions are such that [patients] are receiving fluids
and medicines while seated. In many units, there is no place to
attend patients currently. Beginning this week, tents will be erected
in front of the overcrowded units that will serve as ambulatory
clinics, where patients can receive fluids and other assistance.

Dengue is a disease that is combated by prevention, eliminating
breeding places of the mosquito [vector]. Therefore, official
inspection was strengthened. In Goiania, almost 1000 agents are in
the field, working in collaboration with urban cleanup companies and
public works.

When the resident does not cooperate with the inspection, their homes
are being opened by court authorization. Any vessel that can
accumulate water is removed and taken to the garbage truck at the
same time. Just this week [week of 18 Jan 2010], the goal is to
inspect more than 68 000 properties, and the whole population is
being called upon to collaborate..

--
